reviews.text: Accidentally found this coffee shop. The friendly couple who runs the shop are very passionate about coffee. Nice selection of hot and cold coffee as well as some sweet and savory bakes. I had the cold sparkling Americano which was very nice. Note: more of a takeaway cafe.

This place is just opposite to my condominium and is a life saver. I buy fresh sourdough twice a week and the owner is very friendly and hospitable.
Worth trying everything here and especially the sourdough bread
Passed by at a cosy afternoon for a nice coffee and tasty sour dough pastry. The banana cake gives the unique balance on sweetness and a must try.

A small coffee shop in Pasir Panjang, conveniently located by the bus stop.
The place is quite small and does have some stools to sit but it's more for order on the go.

Ordered flat white twice was really happy with the coffee taste and quality. The service was also very warm and friendly. Pricing wise is moderate, a cup of flat white cost $5.50... It is still reasonable for the quality.

They also sell some pastries, tried the pain au chocolat, it was just OK. They also have cheese cakes, which was recommended by the barista. May try next time when I'm craving for some dessert.

I'm wondering if they could make Magic or Piccolo latte, will try asking on the next visit.
